Church members around the country are free to start attending services. The South African Council of Churches has dismissed claims that places of worship are being reopened prematurely but some denominations, like the Zion Christian Church, have decided to remain closed. So are safety measures in place? Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Some places of worship are preparing to resume services Sunday. The last time gatherings were allowed was just before the start of the lockdown in March. Churches are allowed to hold their services under strict conditions. READ: Lockdown level 3: Some Methodist churches may reopen They are only allowed no more than 50 congregants. But some churches are opting not to open for now, like the Enlightened Christian Gathering. The church headed by Prophet Bushiri Shepherd has over a hundred branches across the country. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.